    <stitle>3300 HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Bumper</title>
            <para>The 3300 Series aerodynamic bumper (
                <hotlnk document="s09010_3.xml" xrefid="f0901002">Figure 2</hotlnk>) is attached to the chassis bumper
                mounting brackets utilizing (4) four mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk document="s09010_3.xml" xrefid="f0901002">Figure 2, Item 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prior to removing the front bumper assembly, park bus on smooth flat surface, put
                    transmission in park position, set parking brake and place wheel chocks at wheels.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch the hood latches each side, tilt the hood forward. Locate the hood harness and
                    chassis harness connection located on the driver side along side of the power steering gear (
                    <hotlnk document="s09010_21.xml" xrefid="f0901024">Figure 22, Item 3</hotlnk>). Disconnect the
                    chassis harness from the hood harness.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the chassis is equipped with an external power connection plug for the engine heater,
                    locate the plug assembly at the lower bumper opening at the center of the bumper. Unplug the
                    connection at the rear of the plug assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the hood to the closed position to access the bumper mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the bumper mounting bolts. Beginning at the upper two bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901020">Figure 20, Item 1</hotlnk>), loosen bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen both lower bumper bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901020">Figure 20, Item 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With an assistant supporting the bumper, remove the two remaining lower bolts. Remove
                    bumper.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901020" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901020.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Bumper Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. UPPER BUMPER MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. LOWER BOLT LOCATION (PASSENGER SIDE SHOWN)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
